Slovenian home appliance maker
Gorenje Group d.d. bought a former factory in eastern  Serbia  for
1.15 million euros ($1.59 million) as part of its plan to
develop an assembly line for washing machines and dryers,
 Vecernje Novosti  newspaper reported, citing local authorities.  The purchase of the 18,000 square-meter (193,700 square
feet) facility in the city of Zajecar is part of Gorenjeâ€™s 2.9
million-euro investment, its third in Serbia, where it plans to
employ 300 workers with subsidies from the Serbian government,
